tool_description: A file management API that allows users to upload files, retrieve file metadata, and generate progressive download URLs.
title: Veestream

api_list.name: Get files
api_list.description: Get all the files that are related to your storage container.

required_parameters.name: apikey
required_parameters.description: The API key related to your account. You can get this by making a request to the  /generate-api-key endpoint

api_list.name: Generate API key
api_list.description:
The /generate-api-key endpoint is a POST method that generates an API key for a user by accepting their email and password in the request body. This endpoint is used to authenticate the user and generate a unique API key that will be used to authorize all subsequent requests made to the API.

Upon successful authentication, the API key will be returned in the response body. This API key should be included in the header of all subsequent requests made by the user to the API. The purpose of the API key is to ensure that only authorized users can access the API and its resources.

To summarize, the /generate-api-key endpoint is used to authenticate a user, generate an API key, and provide the API key for subsequent requests. This endpoint is an essential part of the security mechanism used to protect the API and its resources from unauthorized access.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://veestream2.p.rapidapi.com/generate-api-key"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "veestream2.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: Upload a  file
api_list.description:
This API endpoint enables users to upload a single file at a time. To use this endpoint, you will need to provide an API key in the apikey header of the request. The API key must be valid and obtained from the `/generate-api-key` endpoint.

In addition to the API key, you will also need to include the file to be uploaded in the request body. The file should be provided as a binary data, with the key set to file. You will also need to include the name of the file as a string in the request body.

Example request body format:
`
{
  "file": <binary data>,
  "name": "example_filename"
}`

Once the API receives the request, it will verify the API key and process the file upload. If the API key is valid and the file is uploaded successfully, the API will return a response with a status code of 200.

Please note that only one file can be uploaded per request. If you need to upload multiple files, you will need to make separate requests for each file.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: The name of your file. Give your file a valid string as a name.

required_parameters.name: file
required_parameters.description: A valid file. It can be mp4, mp3, png or any valid file. You can use the HTML5 input to choose the file from your computer.

api_list.name: Generate video gif
api_list.description: This endpoint generates gif image from a video file. You can pass start and end in the query to specify where you want your gif to start and end.

required_parameters.name: id
required_parameters.description: The unique id for the video. After uploading a file you get _id as part of the response. Use _id as your id

optional_parameters.name: apikey
optional_parameters.description: The apikey you got after calling the /generate-api-key endpoint

optional_parameters.name: start
optional_parameters.description: Where you want your gif to start (secs)

optional_parameters.name: end
optional_parameters.description: Where you want your gif to end (secs)

api_list.name: Get video thumbnail
api_list.description: This endpoint generates a thumbnail from a video file. It will only work for video files. The start and end values in the query lets you specify where you want to screenshot your video.

required_parameters.name: id
required_parameters.description: The id parameter is the unique identifier for your file. It is the _id from the upload response.

optional_parameters.name: start
optional_parameters.description: Where you want your the image to be shot from. E.g 10  for 10 secs.

optional_parameters.name: end
optional_parameters.description: The section of the video to take the shot from will be from start to end where start is what you provide in the start query and end is what you put here.

api_list.name: Get file metadata
api_list.description: This endpoint returns metadata about a particular file. The metadata includes the name, _id, url, gif and poster. The latter 2 are useful for videos since they are endpoints to generate gifs and image thumbnails from videos. For non video files, this endpoints will be not useful. We have intentionally decided to let them be in the response for non video files though they do nothing.

api_list.name: Get File progressive download url
api_list.description:
A GET request that allows you to download a file from your storage container that has your files. The file can be an image, video, or any other file type. In order to access the endpoint, you need to pass an "apikey" header in the request headers.

To use this endpoint, replace "{id}" with the "_id" property of the file you want to download. This will return a valid file URL that you can use to download the file.

Overall, this endpoint provides a simple and secure way to download files from your container with the added benefit of being able to work with a variety of file types.
